messages.content: Polaris wakes up in his mindspace, feeling a bit.. warmer than usual. Not the fuzzy kind, either. He feels *physically hot.* Did he fall asleep in the shower? How do you even do that?
He looks around, searching for something to at least lay his head on while he waits for himself to wake up, but then remembers his mind is pretty much the equivalent of a black hole. Hm.

*What the fuck—*
He suddenly felt something intruding in his mindspace. The hell?
There's a soft humming as thin, shining tendrils start unfurling from seemingly nowhere, twisting slowly though the otherwise empty space.
“...Malachite...?” he asks quietly, recognizing the tentacles as something only Malachite has— er, at least *these* ones being the thing only Malachite has.
A soft noise echoes through the space, just barely recognizable as a voice.

“...”
Polaris gets up from the hard, cold ground and approaches the tentacles, reaching a hand out to them. *Mala..?*
One of them curls around his hand loosely. It doesn't quite feel like Hierophant's semi-corporeal tendrils, it's more... solid? Organic? Something closer to an actual octopus. Gross.

“...Hm.”
He grips the tendril that looped his hand and brings it to his lips, kissing it softly. This is Malachite, after all. He can sense it.

"Polaris?"
Malachite appears behind him, voice warping from the merging of dream spaces.

He stiffens up, jumping a bit from the new voice, turning around swiftly.
“...That’s new.”

"...Yeah..."
He seems a little sleepy and out of it, probably due to his just having drifted off. He yawns, sharp teeth flashing.
"Hm... 'm not sure if I've been here before..."

Polaris tries, but fails to fight back the yawn that bubbles out of his own chest, contagious from Malachite’s.
“It’s, uh, my mindscape. We’re asleep. Did you move us to the bed?”

"Did I..."
He runs a hand through his damp hair, trying to remember.
"Ah- no."

He shrugs. 
"You seemed peaceful."
“Just.. use Hierophant to carry us..? The bath is hard and cold.”
"...I'm asleep."

“You could’ve done it while you were awake.”
He looks down.
“And not naked.”
"I didn't wanna wake you up! You were the one that passed out on top of me."

He squints his eyes at Malachite. “I— Weren’t you the one proud of yourself for being able to pick me up with Hierophant? Right now I’m just kinda cold,” he mentions, spreading his arms out for emphasis.
"...Fair enough, but I'm still asleep."
He.. breathes in, and then out, and then lets himself fall back onto the ground, arms and legs spread out lazily. “Well, now I’m cold, and it’s your responsibility to warm me up.”

"I think I'm up to the task,"
He chuckles, padding over and kneeling beside him.
"You better be. Wet and cold isn't a good combo."

"Mhm."
He flops on top of him, ignoring the absurdity of literally every part of this scenario. Fuck it. Glitter tentacle purgatory cuddles.

"..."
After a moment, he hums awkwardly. "This feels a bit awkward. I wish you grabbed a *towel* or something, at least."

"You're on top of me,"
He reminds him.
"I can't wrap a towel around my waist if I already have a *you* there."
"You should've moved me," he shoots back, wondering why the hell Malachite didn't just.. carry the two of them to the bed.

"You were so cute sleeping though,"
He hums, cozying up to him.
"You're out there cuddling me in your sleep like I'm a teddy bear or something."

"..M' not.." 
He trails off, considering it useless to fight against Malachite now. He lets his back hit the floor again, not feeling like getting up.
*Fffffuck me, this is the hardest thing I've ever cuddled on.*

He snuggles him closer, trying to cover as much of him as possible for warmth transferral purposes.
"...If you really want me to get up, you can punch me I guess. Wake me up yourself."

"I.. don't think that's how it works, in a mindspace."
*Plus we're already asleep. I'm uncomfortable, but what's the point of getting up now?*
"Mmm... worth a shot though, right?"
“You’re asking me to *punch* you.”
"Yeah?"
"...I don't *want* to *punch you.*"
"You've punched me before. I can handle it."

"I.. That's because I wasn't thinking."
*We're in my* mindspace *now. I think that means I can think enough to not want to punch you.*
"...We spar all the time? That's you punching me on purpose."
"That's *sparring.* This is waking you up."
"Okay? I can take a hit."

He looks down.
"Still don't want to hurt you.."

"Hmm... oh, wait. Stupid. I'll just pinch myself."
He sticks his tongue out and sits up, straddling him.
"Any last words before I go?"
He looks up at Malachite for a second, thinking "Hm.. Come clothed next time."
"...We're in the shower."
"Put me on the bed and then put some underwear on, or something," he shrugs.

"You're not wearing clothes either,"
He retorts.
"We're *both* asleep in the fucking shower."

"..."
He covers his area.

He looks flabbergasted.
"I... what? Why would you be embarrassed about this."
"It's.. weird. I'm shy about it, I think."
"Why? I've seen it before. It's not *bad."*

"I didn't *say* it was bad—"
*Wait. Maybe I've been implying that it's bad. A little bit.*
"It's just.. It feels personal, for some reason."

He stares at him. 
*"We're dating. We are in a relationship."*

"B-But—"
He doesn't know where he's going with this. The mindscape around them grows a little pinkish.

He chuckles and leans down to give him a kiss.
"Whatever. I'll take us to bed now."
"Please do," he murmurs, tilting his head up and meeting Malachite halfway.

"Mm, alright. Love you."
He smiles at him, then digs his nails into his own arm and vanishes, melting away into nothing.

"Oof," he lets out, his head hitting the hard floor after Malachite vanishes.
"..."
It feels a lot colder now.
As Malachite drifts off, he feels himself resurfacing in the blank *emptiness* of Polaris' mindscape. He shivers a bit, still somewhat unaccustomed to the strange space.

Polaris lifts up his head, immediately feeling the warmth of another life in his mind. He turns his head towards Malachite and his mood is instantly lifted as he rushes over to mala, hugging the other like a lost puppy finding its owner.

"Oof-"
He chuckles and hugs him back, knocked back a bit by the enthusiastic embrace.

"It's cold without you here," he mumbles, struggling to keep his tail from moving side to side violently.
"Thanks for coming back.. and having something on," he says, taking note of the fact that there isn't something poking his leg with gratefulness.

"Mhm."
He purrs, leaning against him.
"Your, uh, dream place is kinda... empty."
"I didn't know it could me.. *not* empty."

"Well, yeah. Mine's weird, but it has *stuff* in it."
As if to illustrate this, a tentacle idly winds its way around their legs.
"What kinda stuff?" he asks, not minding the tendril.

He shrugs.
"Octopuses? I... I *think?* And some plants, or something."

"Lucky..."
*Wish I had sea creatures in here...*
Suddenly, a small pond appeared to the side of them, a few koi fish and cattail plants on the side.

He looks over at the pond, then back at Polaris, grinning ear to ear.
"See? Now your thing has shit in it too."
He hums, pulling him over to investigate.

"A-Ah—" he stutters, not sure what to make of the situation. How the hell did he do that...?
The pond has about 3 koi, one being strangely bigger than the others. The pond also has a few lilpads, with sakura-looking flowers on top of them, as well as just loosely floating about. The koi themselves are black and redish-orange.
"Utsuri koi...?"

"Looks like it."
He crouches next to the pond, peering at the fish.

Polaris crouches down next to Malachite, his eyes curiously following the patterns the koi swim in.
"..They're pretty."

"Mhm..."
He swats at one idly, eyes a bit glazed with sleep.

It moves away quickly, startled by the oncoming hand.
"Hey.." Polaris protests, moving his head to glare at Malachite.

He looks up at him and shrugs. 
"Dream fish."

"They're still fish," he reminds Malachite, staring back into the pond. The water itself was brightly colored, a star contrast to the dark world around them. Its shadows were purple, its highlights green, and the base color itself was a nice sky blue. The cattail plants had coffee-colored tips, the leaves of the plants being a light forest green.
"I.. I think this is here because of you."

He cocks his head at him.
"You were the one that wanted fish."

"Well, yeah, but I've thought of fish a lot of times before. This never happened."
His pupils dilated as the fish slowly approached them again, swimming in large circles and just generally vibing.
"Maybe you just didn't know they *could* happen? Try making something else."

"Hm. Uh.."
He tries thinking of something, *anything* that would be nice. Hm.. A shrine?
A nice, quaint looking shrine appears not too far off to the left of the pond, a small bell with a large rope hanging from the overhang.

He smiles at the sudden appearance of the structure, turning to Polaris once it's done.
"See? *You* did that."

“...Huh. Didn’t realize you could do that..” he murmurs, heading over to the shrine. There isn’t any indication for what kind of god it’s a shrine for— it’s really average. But it’s something.
“Looks kinda like the shrine near the high school on earth..”

"It does seem familiar,"
He murmurs,
"I'm not the best at making shit in my own dreams. My mindscape is a little... weird, for that."
“At least yours *had* stuff before. I think I’m only able to make stuff now because you’re here with me,” he points out, grabbing onto Malachite’s hand and holding it.

Shrug.
"Maybe."
He shrugs back. “I think so.”

"Who knows."
He returns his attention to the fish, humming softly.

After a moment of taking in the silence, Polaris yawns. “Is it possible to get tired while you’re asleep..?” he asks, mostly to himself.
*Maybe I’m just sleeping restlessly.*

"I don't know... dreams don't make any sense-"
He's cut off by a yawn.
"I know *I'm* always tired in here."

“Hm.”
*If we fell asleep, would we fall into a double dream, or would it just make us wake up? If I* were *to fall asleep here, would I toss and turn in the real world or would I toss and turn in my mindscape?*
He let the thoughts drift into his head, mindlessly staring into the pond.
"Hmm... *can* we fall asleep here? Where would we even *go?"*

".."
He closes his eyes and tries thinking of something comfortable— soft and fluffy, like a bed maybe..?
When his eyes are open again, nothings there.
"I think I've run out of mind-energy or whatever.. You try making something."
"Alright. What kind of something?"

A shrug.
"Anything."

"That's- hm."
He thinks for a moment, brow furrowing in concentration as he tries to materialize something. Slowly, an easel oozes out of the ground, forming itself from nothing.

"Huh. Quaint."
Polaris walks up to the easel, sturdy and simple.

"It's the first thing I thought of. Do you want me to try something else?"
He walks over to the easel as well and taps on the wood. Huh.

Another shrug.
"This is new to me. I'm not like you— new opportunity doesn't exactly give me inspiration."
"I don't usually make shit either. I mainly just float around in my dreamscape."

He turns to Malachite, mouth slightly parted in confusion.
"I.. You can float?"
"I guess...? Mine doesn't really have a floor."
"Mine feels boring now," he mumbles, looking around. It's as if there's no end to the space, no ceiling, no walls, only a black floor and black sky.

"You have fish."
He gestures to the pond.
"And you have a floor. I don't have one of those."
"It didn't have a fish before. This floor was the only thing here, he points out, sitting down. "I don't exactly like it here."
"Mm. Well, now you have shit! *And* you can make *more* shit. Do you want a bed or something?"

"I tried thinking up one earlier, but nothing appeared," he shrugged.
"My mindscape doesn't usually listen to me. This whole "creating stuff" thing is new."

"Yours is a lot easier to use than mine. Here, let me..."
He trails off, closing his eyes and exhaling as he envisions a bed.

A small 'oh' escapes his mouth as the bed Malachite imagines appears.
"...This feels clustered already."
*But, I guess if I wanted to reset it or something I could just... walk away to a new area.*

He walks up to it and pokes it. Seems solid enough.
"...Yep, this is a bed."

"A pool, a shrine, an easel and a bed. Huh."
Polaris follows Malachite to the bed, sitting on it experimentally. It's fluffy as shit.

"Pretty good stuff."
He flops onto it face-first, tail swishing.

*Oh. Guess it's sturdy enough to lay on then.*
He lays on his back next to Malachite, smiling as he contently watches Malachite's tail swishing back and forth.
"Hm. If you bit my neck here, would it appear in the real world?"

"Hmm?"
He looks over at him.
"I don't see why it would. This place isn't *real."*

"Yeah, but.. Hm."
*If you get hurt in the real world, it hurts in here. Not the other way around.*
"My brain kinda shut off for a second, sorry."
"Don't apologize. You're literally asleep."

"Ah. Yeah, guess I am."
He looks up into the almost pitch black sky, examining it. It's a wonder how you can see anything with a sky so dark.
"Hm. Do you think I can imagine stars for the sky?"

"Stars?"
He flips over to look up at the sky, propping himself up on his elbows.
"You can certainly *try."*

He stays quiet again, slowly letting his eyes shut as he imagines a bright, starry sky with nice, ocean-like colors. As he does, the image finds its way into the sky, each star forming split seconds away from each other, growing out into the infinite vast of darkness.

Malachite stares at the display, mouth agape slightly.
"...Huh."

He peeks an eye just a little, scared it didnt work, before both snap open wide and he sits up, amazed at the sight.
*...Holy shit.*
His tail starts thumping behind him excitedly and his ear flicks a bit.

He stares at the stars for a while, enraptured, before turning to Polaris and grinning at how *excited* he looks. 
"Beautiful..."

"Mhm," he nods, looking all around. Multiple groups of stars form images of marine life, from starfist to dolphins to whales. "It's... *wow.*"
*Maybe my mindspace.. isn't so bad.*

The stars combined with the slow, undulating tentacles leaking in from Malachite's dreamscape give the whole place a surreal quality, but it's somehow calming. Despite the inherently unsettling nature of it all, it feels *safe.*
After a moment of enjoying the stars, Polaris turned himself over, facing and hugging Malachite close to him, nuzzling his face into his neck.

He purrs, leaning his head back to give him space. 
"Mmm, 's nice here."
“Y’know..” he murmurs into Malachite’s neck, planting a small kiss on it. “I think you improve me.”

"Hmm?"
He hums, melting into his touch.
"I think *you* improve *me.* I'm a disaster without you."
He plants a few more kisses, humming with content purrs. “Nah. Without you, I’d still hate my own mind. It feels wrong without you here, I think.”

"You have stars now,"
He purrs,
"That's nice."
“Was only able to create em because you’re here.”

"Fair enough."
He rests his hands on Polaris' waist, pulling him closer.

He pressed one more lingering kiss into Malachite’s neck before turning his face to the stars again, sighing at the breathtaking sight. “Hm. Read in a poem book somewhere that it’s every romantics dream to make love under the stars.”

He glows, casting green light over both of them.
"...Is that an invitation?"
He purrs.
A small shrug. “If you want it to be. The stars and the position we’re in just made me think about it, I guess. Am I a romantic? Maybe. I dunno.”
He was feeling talkative today.

"That *does* sound romantic."
He shuffles over and lays down on top of Polaris, rumbling softly.
"...Hm. You actually know what you're talking about this time, right?"
He gives Malachite a small, shy smile. “Yeah. I think.”

He stares at him wide-eyed, his heart doing somersaults in his chest.
"...I love you."
He flutters his eyes shut, letting himself smile a bit wider and leaning up to bump their foreheads together. “Love you, too.”

"Mmm."
He nuzzles against him, pressing a small kiss onto his collarbone.
“Mmm..” he hums back, a small purr forming in his chest. “I never remember my dreams. But I want to remember this one, because you’re here. And it feels like reality whenever you’re here with me.”

"I'm with you in the real world too,"
He murmurs, laying his head against him and listening to the slow thrumming of his pulse.
"When you wake up, I'll be next to you, just like this."
“Please tell me I won’t be naked.”

He chuckles.
"I put some shorts on you, don't worry."
He lets out a relieved sigh. "Oh thank god."
"...Do you think we can just... make clothes? In the dream, I mean."
"Mm.. Probably. Too tired to care right now, though."

"Fair enough."
He brushes another kiss over him, sighing. *God, he loves him.*
"...You look *beautiful* in this starlight."
"You look even more. You glow, whether you're flustered or not, and the lighting brings that out even more," he sighs back, moving his head to the side and laying his chin on top of malachite's hair.

"You look like the stars..."
He nuzzles into him, pressing his lips over his carotid artery and letting them linger, feeling Polaris' pulse throughout his own body.
His breath hitches as he lets out a small, surprised gasp, wrapping his arms around Malachie's back and holding him close as he lingers on the sensitive spot.
He hums at the closeness and flicks his tongue out over the skin, just barely brushing against him.
"Mm.. Feels nice," he hums again, beginning to pant a bit. Making out hits different when its in your mindspace and under the stars.

*"You* feel nice..."
He mumbles, licking a longer stripe up his neck.

"G-Glad you think s-soo..hh.." he slurs, tilting his head more to the side to let Mala do this thing. It's only been a few days, but it feels like its been a *lifetime* since they've done this.
And it's a first in the mindscape.

"Your voice is so nice, Polaris,"
He shivers a little, trailing kisses up to his jaw.
He lets out a small whimper, lips parted and sighing at the oh so light kisses pressed along his neck. "G-Glad you think so.. yours is j-just as incredible."
He plants an open-mouthed kiss under his ear, rumbling happily .

He gasped a bit, biting his lip to stop anymore whimpers from spilling out, before remember that there's absolutely zero chance anyone would hear him in the mindspace except Malachite, but still being embarrassed anyways.

"You can be loud,"
He pulls away to murmur into his ear.
"There's nobody else listening."
"Th-That's obvious," he mumbles, blinking a little bit. He's a *tiny* bit out of it. Tiny bit.

"I wanna hear you."
He gently nibbles at his earlobe, purring.
"A-*Hhah—*" he breaths out, feeling embarrassed and biting his lip again after.

He pulls back and looks at Polaris, smiling ear to ear.
"Your voice is *beautiful*, baby," 
He kisses his cheek before nestling himself back into the crook of his neck.
His cheeks blush a bit brighter than before at the pet name and he squeezes his eyes shut, whimpering again.

"So lovely,"
He coos between kisses, moving one hand into his hair.
Another soft, affectionate sigh makes its way out of his chest, tilting his head up into the touch of his hand.

"You're so sensitive..."
He speaks softly against his skin, muffled in between little pecks and licks.
"It's sweet."
"I-If you aren't t— *hhah* touched in a-fffectionate ways for a-lmost two m-million years, y-y'get a lil se-nssitive..." he mumbles, his words stumbling in his daze.

"Poor thing..."
He croons, whimpering very softly himself.
"Mm, do you want me to bite you, Polaris?"
He thinks about it for a second.. the first time, it hurt after he bit too deep, but.. guess it couldn't hurt to try again. He nods.

He smiles against him.
"M'kay, I'll be gentle this time."
He kisses at him for a little longer, then nibbles at his neck lightly, careful not to break the skin.
His breath hitches, himself shutting his eyes tight from the feeling of it all. He bites his lip, drawing a bit of blood from the lower.

He pulls himself up to look at him.
"Is this alright? I don't want to go overboard again."
He doesn’t open his eyes, but he does relax them to let Malachite know that he’s okay. “It’s... fine. It’s fine, j-just.. don’t go too deep, alright?”
"Mhm. Tell me if it's too much, okay?"
He hums.
Comforted by the confirmation that Polaris is alright, he leans back in and latches onto the same spot, pricking the skin with his teeth and sucking a dark mark into it.

"Hh*aAHh*—"
He lets out a sharp noise of surprise, still not exactly being *used* to the sharp canines. He whimpers especially as Malachite sucks into it.

He laps up the little beads of blood, then moves up to give Polaris a peck on the lips.
"Still okay?"
Another whimper. "Mhm. Ff-felt nice.."

"That's good,"
He coos, leaning in for another kiss.

Suddenly, Polaris feels a sharp pain in his chest and his head, where the large crack is. 
"M—Ma-ala—" His eyes widen, pupils dilated, and he rushes his chest forward, curling in on himself and clutching his face.

"Polaris?"
He sits up, alarmed. *Shit. Shit. Fuck.*
*"Polaris?* Shit, are you okay?"

He blinks, confused and unfocused. *I can’t see. It’s hard to see.*
“S-Scar.. th-ey h-hhurt..” he whimpers out, letting out another groan as his scars shine, looking not un-similar to the galaxy above them. The mindscape around them rumbles.

"Shit-"
*Is it something he did? Oh god-*
"Shit, does- has this happened before? Is there anything I can do to help?"

“D-Don’t know..” he mumbles out, squeezing his eyes as small tears peck at them.
*Why does this hurt so bad? Why now, when I’m with Malachite, finally able to relax? I thought I was done with these. I thought I got over them. Why do they still hurt?*
In the distance, something on the ground glows bright.

He whips his head toward the light.
"Hey- I'm going to go look at that thing. Can you sit here?"
He looks up at Malachite, eyes glazed over and tense, before he hugs himself and gives Malachite a shaky nod, bending his legs and burying his face into his knees.

He lingers for a moment before rushing over to the glowing... whatever it is. *Shit.* Did *he* do this? Did he hurt him somehow? Fuck, did he pressure Polaris into his weird biting shit and mess him up?

At a certain point, the cracks appear. They’re small, just a vast amount of hairline cracks, but they snake on. None of them are separate rom each other, connected at one point or another. As Malachite continues on, they get bigger and thicker and deeper, glowing brighter and brighter.

*Oh god...*
He crouches next to one of the rifts and inspects it, looking at it with horror.

Somewhere ahead of Malachite, a whiles away, three figures appear. Two of them are shrouded in shadow, with a tall, lanky one leaning down, hands on the shoulders of the other shrouded figure, who appears to be smaller. In front of those figures, though...
(:blur: :blur: :blur:)

"Who are you?"
He peers at them, trying to make out more detail.

The only figure that was even close to being lucid was blurry— *distorted.* It was larger than the smaller shrouded figure, but smaller than the bigger one. It was screaming.

The distorted figures themselves were talking, but it was muffled, and listening to them felt as if listening to someone through plugged ears.

*”Do y.... see th............os? ........hy you should.............Mo.....se would have h...........one anyways.”*

*"Who are you?"*
He summons Hierophant and moves toward them cautiously.
(I am... No longer upset :blur:)

The figures pay no mind to him. They continue on, the largest one letting go of the smallest and circling the screaming figure. The screaming one itself looks like a *mess—* knotted, wrangled curlly hair. It’s wearing a bland turtleneck with a loosened collar and regular seeming pants and shoes. Malachite can’t see their face from the side, as their arms are blocking it, though he could probably see if he walked between the three figures to get a peak.

He storms toward them, intent on finding out *what the fuck is happening.*
"Don't fucking make me ask again! *Who the hell are you?"*

Although the figures didn’t hear Malachite before, they did now. The smaller one turned first, it’s eyes glowing and bright, swirling as if multiple messy sketches of a spiraling circle animated together. It’s most notable features were the braid that made its way from the back of their head, and the large wings that quiver behind them nervously.

The larger one took a big longer. It circled the screaming figure again, before stopping right in front of the figure and slowly turning it’s head towards Malachite, it’s eyes just as bright, but even more distorted— it’s as if the mere *memory* of the person is barely hanging on by a single thread.
He's tired of this bullshit. Hierophant whips toward the figures, trying to grab them.

The tentacle goes through the figures, though with the larger one, the hood on it’s head flies off, the rest of the scarf flowing behind them before settling for after a moment.

If the body of the figures were shrouded in a dark gray before, this figures face is completely black, and looking at it feels like looking in the eyes of insanity itself.

*What the fuck?*
He shudders and steps toward the hooded one, reaching a hand out.
The figure does not move. Though, it cocks its head to the side, as if examining this new being.
He steps back and surveys the taller figure, then turns to look at the screaming one. Maybe he'll have more luck there.

The taller figure steps back, giving Malachite more room to stand *directly* in front of the screaming figure, who has not stopped with it’s sound. Actually, it’s almost as if it’s gotten louder, more intense. More hurt. More *scared*.
He glances back at the taller figure, suspicious, then crouches down beside the screaming figure to investigate.

The person’s eyes were wide, in fear? Pain? You couldn’t tell. The large vertical scar over their right eye seemed familiar, but... the untouched one on the left didn’t. They curled in on themself more.
He reaches out towards them. *What the fuck?*
The figure, somehow, whimpers through all the screams, curling in further, almost in a ball. It’s face is almost unseeable now, as it’s just curling in further and further.
He tries to touch it, to see if it's corporeal, but hesitates. *Might as well test this on one of the not screaming ones first.* He stands and looks at the two others, considering.

Although the expressions on these beings are invisible, they radiate certain... *energies.* The smaller one feels scared, guilty, not exactly curled in on itself but not presenting itself either. The taller one, on the other hand, feels *smug,* as if its won something.
He doesn't want to harass the smaller one, so he reaches out for the tall one. Bastard energies.

On the taller’s pitch black face, similar to the eyes, a bright, white, not-so-right smile forms, wide and threatening and *wrong,*
His lip curls involuntarily in disgust, and he recoils slightly. This figure feels *horrible*, but he continues for the sake of science. He attempts to touch the tall figure.

The figure lets him, as if it *chose* to be more corporeal for the sake of the hesitant contact. When he does, a million different, gore-filled deaths field his vision, looping together as if multiple projectors playing different movies on the same screen.

***"Shit-"***
He reels backwards, looking at the figure with horror. *What the FUCK.*
***"Who are you?"***

From his place on the bed farther away, Polaris whimpers.

The shrouded figure says nothing. It only smiles wider and bows, deep and dramatic.

He whips his head around to look at Polaris, then looks back at the figure. That *pisses him off.*
"What the fuck are you *doing?* Stop fucking around."
They stay silent.

*If he's awake, he can wake Polaris up. Maybe getting him away from here will help.*
"If you aren't going to be useful, fine. I'm waking us up."
He announces, preparing to dig his nails into his arm again.

The figure slowly looks up at him again. It speaks, its voice slow and distorted, as if the mindscape itself isn’t sure if it’s projecting the sound correctly.

*“Go ahead, little Malachite..”* it said with a creepy smile, eyes squinting in delight.
